 NEWS
 ==============================

 [1.0.0] - 2024-03-10

 This is an extensive rewrite of former SYSeg.

 Main changes:
  
 - REUSE 3.0 compliance with SPDX standard.
 - Revised build scripts with extended dependency check.
 - Improved, more detailed, install guide
 - New code examples and programming exercises.
 - New code export tools

 Known issues:

 - Provisional use of a custom local install of the reuse-tool.
 - Tarball distribution does not pass reuse-tool linting.
 - Some programming exercises need a major revision.
 - Documentation of the code examples needs revisions.

 ------------------------------

 [0.2.1 ] - 2024-03-10

 Mostly bug fixes (still alpha). 

 ------------------------------

 [0.1.1 ] - 2021-05-10

 Mostly bug fixes (still alpha).

 - Extensive redesign of existing code examples.
 - Removal of error-prone exercises for future revision.
 - New code examples and programming exercises.
 
 ------------------------------

 [0.1.0] - 2021-05-01

 Initial, non-stable release. Evertying may change.

 

